I left Portugal at 4.30 this morning.

01:26.618 --> 01:28.507
It's the alcohol that's keeping me going.

01:28.627 --> 01:29.874
And where about in Portugal?

01:29.994 --> 01:30.936
Loriga.

01:30.963 --> 01:33.543
It's a little village in the mountains.

01:33.615 --> 01:35.128
It's really hot in the summer.

01:35.677 --> 01:37.400
Ski country in the winter, I'd...

01:37.453 --> 01:39.219
live there and bake bread, if I could.

01:39.646 --> 01:40.680
I'll stick to beer.

01:42.130 --> 01:44.069
A Frenchman who doesn't drink wine?

01:45.350 --> 01:47.162
I drink wine just not tonight.

01:47.760 --> 01:48.978
Are your kids bilingual?

01:49.170 --> 01:49.805
No.

01:50.136 --> 01:51.893
No, they probably should be, but,

01:52.013 --> 01:53.455
when they were growing up, we didn't

01:53.650 --> 01:55.880
speak much French in the house.

01:56.769 --> 01:57.873
I always thought

01:57.993 --> 01:59.349
if I ever had kids,

01:59.826 --> 02:02.328
it'd be really nice for
them to have two languages:

02:02.409 --> 02:05.552
you know, mom's language,
and dad's language.

02:05.672 --> 02:08.463
Little cultural citizens of the world.

02:09.112 --> 02:10.829
But then I hooked up with Nelson, and...

02:12.023 --> 02:13.359
well, he's barely got any English.

02:15.679 --> 02:18.077
Sonny married beneath herself.

02:19.243 --> 02:20.174
Where are you from?

02:21.232 --> 02:22.222
Not London.

02:23.939 --> 02:24.747
Corby.

02:25.678 --> 02:28.026
Old steel town in the
middle of the country.

02:28.553 --> 02:29.652
I'm a mick-mack.

02:29.870 --> 02:30.960
I don't know what that is.

02:30.992 --> 02:33.299
Half-Irish, half-Scottish.
Second generation.

02:33.331 --> 02:35.736
They all followed the heavy
industry to England, and stayed.

02:35.928 --> 02:37.213
It can be a difficult mix.

02:37.280 --> 02:38.893
The Celt and the steel,

02:38.947 --> 02:40.237
and the displacement...

02:41.218 --> 02:42.657
hard to penetrate really.

02:44.247 --> 02:45.631
Do you go back?

02:47.680 --> 02:51.476
My brother and I, we were...
put into care, as kids.

02:51.604 --> 02:52.864
I didn't see him or years,

02:52.880 --> 02:55.584
but I eventually shipped down
here when I was in my teens.

02:55.636 --> 02:58.481
But Corby, I was born there,
I wouldn't call it home.

02:58.481 --> 03:00.839
- Care can mess kids up.
- Yeah it can.

03:01.480 --> 03:03.808
My brother and I spent some years in care.

03:04.308 --> 03:05.052
What?

03:08.038 --> 03:09.372
What shall we toast?

03:10.087 --> 03:11.387
How about...

03:12.988 --> 03:14.447
absent friends.

03:19.919 --> 03:22.740
36 HOURS EARLIER

03:35.859 --> 03:37.289
You need a piss?

03:43.726 --> 03:45.185
Really, you're making me nervous.

03:45.906 --> 03:46.940
I can't sleep.

03:47.774 --> 03:49.966
When I do, eventually, I just see his face

03:50.086 --> 03:51.402
right there, all the time.

03:52.168 --> 03:54.177
- Who are you talking about?
- Victor!

03:54.773 --> 03:57.200
I just keep on hearing his
phone call over and over.

03:57.320 --> 03:58.815
He was probably wasted.

03:59.678 --> 04:01.449
The guy can't hold his liquor, you know.

04:01.846 --> 04:05.280
Yeah, he's a friendly type
of murdering necrophiliac.

04:06.530 --> 04:08.470
- What are we gonna do?
- Lay low.

04:10.122 --> 04:11.734
I'm not sure we're good at that.

04:33.286 --> 04:34.313
Yeah.

04:39.098 --> 04:40.103
What are you doing?

04:40.126 --> 04:42.391
- I work here.
- Well, it's 6.30!

04:42.754 --> 04:43.464
Yeah.

04:43.719 --> 04:45.080
That's the time I start work.

04:45.138 --> 04:45.904
Really?

04:48.317 --> 04:49.912
Possible new contract.

04:51.183 --> 04:53.193
Didn't want to tie up one of the vans.

04:54.056 --> 04:56.241
- Did you get a haircut?
- No.

05:05.947 --> 05:08.411
- The city that never sleeps.
- That's New York.

05:09.075 --> 05:11.970
- What's London?
- London is The Big Smoke.

05:13.038 --> 05:16.774
- So, what's Paris?
- An overpriced shithole near Disneyland.

05:17.488 --> 05:19.054
Look at you making a joke.

05:19.083 --> 05:20.252
You're evolving.

05:21.388 --> 05:23.908
Hello, we're looking for Nelson Clay.

05:26.576 --> 05:28.023
What's wrong with you?

05:28.466 --> 05:29.573
Battle wound.

05:29.602 --> 05:31.083
You're such a loser.

05:31.344 --> 05:32.796
I never lose.

05:35.026 --> 05:37.019
Can you put the pens away, please?

05:38.898 --> 05:40.056
Knife wound.

05:40.238 --> 05:42.435
- It needs stitches.
- It needs a wash.

05:42.458 --> 05:44.997
She's right. No knife wounds before school.

05:45.026 --> 05:46.325
I'm practising,

05:46.393 --> 05:48.528
in case the French guys show up.

05:49.770 --> 05:51.978
There are no French guys, darling.

05:56.144 --> 05:57.104
Come on.

06:02.440 --> 06:03.432
Where are we going?

06:08.540 --> 06:10.729
You don't have to be such
a dick, man. It's very rude.

06:10.738 --> 06:13.068
I'm not in the mood to chat, lads.

06:13.821 --> 06:15.190
So if you don't mind...

06:36.701 --> 06:37.922
Taste this.

06:45.679 --> 06:46.950
What are you getting?

06:49.371 --> 06:50.571
Ah, um...

06:52.040 --> 06:53.810
- Tangy. -
It's rose-hip.

06:54.171 --> 06:56.974
There's your daily dose of
vitamin C in that one cup.

06:57.568 --> 06:59.646
See, I'm growing these old school

06:59.708 --> 07:01.246
traditional shrubs.

07:01.320 --> 07:04.277
The new ones are bred, so they don't fruit.

07:04.460 --> 07:06.543
People want everything sterile these days.

07:06.809 --> 07:08.445
Are we here for a tea party?

07:09.331 --> 07:10.551
I need your help.

07:11.011 --> 07:12.211
Inside.

07:14.201 --> 07:15.401
What are you reading?

07:16.204 --> 07:18.464
Don't try to be my friend. It won't work.

07:29.589 --> 07:30.789
He's been shot?

07:31.342 --> 07:32.545
Right knee.

07:34.683 --> 07:37.516
Well, I can't fucking do
this. This is way beyond me.

07:37.941 --> 07:40.513
You need to get him to a
hospital, he needs a doctor.

07:41.625 --> 07:43.045
We're not here for that.

07:52.840 --> 07:54.368
You're going to kill him?

07:55.338 --> 07:56.538
Yeah.

07:57.212 --> 07:58.892
This is my death scene, mate.

07:59.876 --> 08:01.213
Joey will kill him.

08:02.161 --> 08:03.365
You will clean it up.

08:03.739 --> 08:05.618
It's just his leg. You can save him.

08:05.652 --> 08:08.439
- You don't understand the bigger picture?
- What? And you do?

08:14.951 --> 08:16.151
Boss.

08:16.930 --> 08:19.734
Denny, put your weapon away. Get some air.

08:21.375 --> 08:23.708
I'll let Frank fill you in himself.

08:25.496 --> 08:27.398
Don't leave anything out now.

08:30.214 --> 08:31.440
Fuck!

08:37.155 --> 08:38.356
What did you do?

08:43.073 --> 08:44.274
Got caught.

08:46.830 --> 08:48.862
I don't suppose you carry
any painkillers, do you?

08:49.038 --> 08:50.238
No, sorry.

08:52.513 --> 08:53.713
Ha!

08:53.715 --> 08:55.117
Last one.

09:02.189 --> 09:04.392
Was this the way out you talked about?

09:05.322 --> 09:06.522
Yeah.

09:07.582 --> 09:08.791
I, um...

09:09.740 --> 09:12.778
I was involved with a
man named Veysel Kisa.

09:12.993 --> 09:15.195
- He's the real deal.
- Turkish.

09:16.506 --> 09:18.468
- They were in Saint-Nazaire.-
They're everywhere.

09:18.638 --> 09:20.489
I sold Veysel some information.

09:21.569 --> 09:22.769
It was good money.

09:23.543 --> 09:24.743
Enough for this?

09:26.273 --> 09:27.473
Maybe not.

09:32.676 --> 09:33.930
Gotta go into London.

09:37.904 --> 09:39.379
Let's finish this thing up.

09:43.610 --> 09:46.010
- He's not really going to kill you.
- Yeah,

09:46.321 --> 09:47.521
he will.

09:48.473 --> 09:49.835
And he'll kill you too.

09:51.027 --> 09:52.230
When it suits him.

09:52.580 --> 09:54.107
Not today, but you know...

09:54.227 --> 09:56.012
Try not to overthink it... it's...

09:56.088 --> 09:57.456
it's just a fact.

10:01.296 --> 10:03.615
Who's been smoking? Huh?

10:04.064 --> 10:06.016
Sonny's got a nose like a beagle!

10:09.769 --> 10:11.599
Let's not make this any more painful.

10:11.673 --> 10:13.800
- You don't have to do this.
- You know I do!

10:13.920 --> 10:16.271
- Bullshit.
- Just to be clear,

10:17.066 --> 10:19.590
this is business, all right?

10:20.024 --> 10:22.873
It's not personal. There is no alternative.

10:23.787 --> 10:25.671
He knew exactly the risk he was taking

10:25.694 --> 10:28.345
when he went squealing
to those fucking Turks!

10:32.850 --> 10:34.059
You're finished.

10:35.781 --> 10:37.825
This isn't part of the agreement.

10:39.171 --> 10:40.374
I said no.

11:01.002 --> 11:02.202
I'm sorry.

11:25.174 --> 11:27.558
I'm afraid I'm gonna have to
leave you to get on with it.

11:28.352 --> 11:31.360
I have some business in town. Joey will
drive you back when you're finished.

11:31.400 --> 11:33.023
Fuck you! I'm not cleaning this!

11:34.307 --> 11:36.160
Joey can drive us back right now.

11:36.280 --> 11:38.530
- Are you sure?
- Positive.

11:39.245 --> 11:40.886
Your partner agrees with you?

11:41.365 --> 11:42.565
Always.

11:46.551 --> 11:47.891
It's been a tough morning.

11:48.011 --> 11:49.577
I'll assume you're emotional.

11:49.591 --> 11:51.553
I'm not an emotional man.

11:52.806 --> 11:55.605
We're not cleaning up the
murder you just committed.

11:56.888 --> 11:58.652
And that's your decision?

11:59.884 --> 12:02.154
This place will remain exactly as it is

12:02.155 --> 12:03.898
until these two change their minds.

12:04.960 --> 12:06.248
Sonny comes back tomorrow,

12:06.368 --> 12:08.224
this place isn't as was,

12:08.344 --> 12:10.153
there will be consequences.

12:13.746 --> 12:15.160
Joey, get the car.

12:30.287 --> 12:32.705
Every rule I insisted on, he breaks:

12:32.740 --> 12:33.960
we're not there for crime,

12:33.977 --> 12:36.395
we don't know details of
what shit has gone down,

12:36.445 --> 12:39.544
we control the scene. And... and
now he's killing guys in front of us?

12:39.731 --> 12:41.310
His own fucking guy.

12:43.007 --> 12:44.657
You don't have anything to say about this?

12:44.964 --> 12:47.309
Yeah. I have something
I want to contribute.

12:47.689 --> 12:49.449
If you say no to Nelson Clay,

12:50.283 --> 12:51.895
we're gonna need new friends.

12:53.190 --> 12:55.227
Well, even for you that
would be very stupid.

12:55.693 --> 12:57.918
I told you not to say
that anymore, all right?

12:58.668 --> 12:59.868
All right?

13:00.046 --> 13:02.305
You're willing to put your family
at risk because your pride is hurt?

13:02.329 --> 13:04.230
It has nothing to do with my pride!

13:04.452 --> 13:07.296
You got a pretty fucking big hide.
You know that? Do you know that?

13:07.319 --> 13:09.895
- Huh?
- We gotta make it stop now,

13:10.116 --> 13:12.640
or we're fucked! Permanently.

13:12.661 --> 13:15.670
He will cut Oliver's balls
before they grow peach fuzz.

13:15.680 --> 13:17.573
and he will let Maddy
live, but he will ruin her!

13:17.574 --> 13:19.327
How are you fucking helping right now?!

13:19.422 --> 13:20.692
How do you ever help?

13:20.721 --> 13:22.520
You go back, you do the job,

13:22.565 --> 13:24.550
- and you buy us time.
- No.

13:25.030 --> 13:26.447
I should rip your fucking

13:26.448 --> 13:28.872
- head off right now.
- Well, anything you wanna try.

13:29.148 --> 13:30.470
Go for it.

14:01.440 --> 14:02.745
You okay?

14:03.091 --> 14:04.963
I dropped 'em off in town.

14:10.613 --> 14:12.688
So what happens if he doesn't do the clean?

14:12.963 --> 14:14.275
He will.

14:14.666 --> 14:16.160
He's just...

14:18.701 --> 14:20.230
overwhelmed.

14:22.890 --> 14:25.051
Denny, go inside, check them out.

14:30.985 --> 14:32.635
Jean Bastière

14:32.643 --> 14:35.526
needs to feel like he has some control.

14:38.506 --> 14:39.721
But he doesn't.

14:39.765 --> 14:41.734
He can always say no.

14:42.072 --> 14:43.880
It's a powerful word.

14:45.353 --> 14:46.799
And then what?

14:49.416 --> 14:50.906
Stay here.

14:53.239 --> 14:54.880
Clear your head.

15:01.753 --> 15:04.919
My husband suffered some
depression. Long-term unemployed.

15:04.920 --> 15:07.323
Doctors got him on this dairy-free diet.

15:07.324 --> 15:09.355
Trouble is, everything tastes like rubber.

15:09.475 --> 15:11.304
Well, it could help I suppose.

15:11.315 --> 15:14.585
Our bodies aren't designed to cope with
all the processed rubbish on the shelves.

15:14.585 --> 15:17.667
True. We try to stay clear of processed.

15:18.731 --> 15:20.659
- Except crisps.
- Hm!

15:20.681 --> 15:22.582
Couldn't live without crisps.

15:23.615 --> 15:25.193
Jean, this is... um...

15:25.313 --> 15:27.770
- DCI Squire.
- Diane Squire.

15:27.827 --> 15:29.547
I hope you don't mind me popping by.

15:29.623 --> 15:30.823
No.

15:31.216 --> 15:32.520
Could we have a quick word?

15:33.463 --> 15:36.187
Of course. Um... could
you just give me 5 minutes?

15:36.187 --> 15:37.387
Sure.

16:03.451 --> 16:04.677
Thank you.

16:05.698 --> 16:07.316
Could we have the room please?

16:08.377 --> 16:10.103
He means "get out".

16:12.685 --> 16:15.540
- Thank you.
- I'll go see a man about a horse.

16:18.390 --> 16:20.360
- Can I offer you a drink?
- No, thanks.

16:20.405 --> 16:22.176
- Mind if I have one?
- Not at all.

16:30.987 --> 16:32.548
Thanks for seeing me.

16:32.699 --> 16:33.899
Uh...

16:34.500 --> 16:36.788
I'm taking over the Met investigation

16:36.788 --> 16:39.476
into the activities of DCI Tom Kendrick.

16:40.719 --> 16:42.632
I know you had dealings with him.

16:43.276 --> 16:44.525
Many people did.

16:44.587 --> 16:46.070
He was head of procurement.

16:46.886 --> 16:48.561
He put a lot of work your way.

16:50.025 --> 16:52.301
He put work everyone's way.

16:52.421 --> 16:55.337
You paid Tom Kendrick back-handers.

16:55.972 --> 16:57.874
I can demonstrate that very clearly.

16:58.861 --> 17:01.285
You weren't alone. Everyone paid him.

17:01.302 --> 17:02.692
I'm not interested in that.

17:04.916 --> 17:08.354
I believe Tom Kendrick was involved
with some serious criminals.

17:08.886 --> 17:12.303
People powerful enough to kill a
police officer and feel protected.

17:13.319 --> 17:14.590
Kendrick was murdered?

17:15.011 --> 17:16.646
You were there, you tell me.

17:19.012 --> 17:22.039
- You did clean the scene.
- Yes, um...

17:22.282 --> 17:24.269
but I understood it was suicide.

17:26.550 --> 17:29.832
The death of a fellow officer
seems to put everyone on edge.

17:30.275 --> 17:32.772
It's early days, but anything you know,

17:32.818 --> 17:35.360
scenes you cleaned,
paperwork you might have,

17:35.377 --> 17:38.005
photographs, logbooks, diaries...

17:38.465 --> 17:40.208
anything you think could help.

17:43.361 --> 17:44.573
Keep in touch.

17:45.845 --> 17:47.496
I'll see myself out.

17:49.290 --> 17:50.490
Thank you.

17:57.931 --> 17:59.353
_

18:08.921 --> 18:11.277
_

18:52.653 --> 18:53.853
Thanks.

18:57.578 --> 18:59.899
- I'm looking for someone.
- Who?

19:01.801 --> 19:03.101
Veysel Kisa.

19:06.564 --> 19:07.881
Are you a friend?

19:08.732 --> 19:11.190
I'm a friend of a friend.
I need to talk to him.

19:15.130 --> 19:17.207
Tell him Frank McElroy is dead.

19:22.048 --> 19:23.411
I know a Veysel.

19:23.921 --> 19:25.590
It might be the same one.

19:26.346 --> 19:28.446
He's kind of difficult to get hold of.

19:32.397 --> 19:33.628
But I can try.

19:35.734 --> 19:37.573
I don't usually take the time

19:37.908 --> 19:39.753
for meet and greets.

19:40.928 --> 19:42.494
But you have my attention.

19:42.840 --> 19:46.406
We've lost £100 000
worth of A-grade heroin.

19:47.160 --> 19:49.600
- That was clumsy.
- We think you have it.

19:49.743 --> 19:50.943
I don't.

19:51.320 --> 19:54.334
We need payment, or our product back.

19:54.351 --> 19:57.360
This is the last time I will repeat myself,

19:57.400 --> 19:59.330
and I do it out of politeness

19:59.341 --> 20:01.805
because you are tourists in my city.

20:02.470 --> 20:03.906
I don't have any heroin.

20:04.128 --> 20:06.132
A-grade or otherwise.

20:06.398 --> 20:07.624
We were told you did.

20:07.675 --> 20:09.655
- You were misinformed.
- Lying fuck!

20:09.656 --> 20:10.840
No, no, no!

20:10.842 --> 20:12.403
Martin Bastière is the lying fuck!

20:12.471 --> 20:15.446
A guy called Martin Bastière
told us that you took it from him.

20:15.480 --> 20:17.057
And it wasn't hard to find you, so,

20:17.177 --> 20:20.520
- we figured that you must be a player.
- You know Martin Bastière.

20:21.059 --> 20:23.136
I don't know any French man.

20:23.307 --> 20:25.371
Do we know any French man, Denny ?

20:25.372 --> 20:27.155
I know a couple Spanish,

20:27.411 --> 20:28.611
a Swede,

20:29.504 --> 20:31.991
no French though. Seen 'em on telly.

20:33.527 --> 20:35.026
No French.

20:38.157 --> 20:39.966
Sounds to me,

20:40.684 --> 20:44.605
like you all need to keep
a closer eye on your heroin.

20:45.243 --> 20:48.134
- Do you think I'm stupid?
- Yes.

20:48.533 --> 20:49.970
Yes, I do.

20:50.865 --> 20:53.428
That is exactly what I think.

20:53.455 --> 20:55.273
Don't talk anymore.

20:56.213 --> 20:57.978
Get on your feet,

20:58.098 --> 21:00.612
- and leave.
- Okay, we go.

21:01.099 --> 21:02.680
Thank you for your time.

21:14.607 --> 21:15.902
Hello?

21:17.428 --> 21:18.811
Hello, who's this?

21:21.357 --> 21:23.645
- Maddy?
- So, you didn't drown.

21:25.800 --> 21:29.480
No, I didn't. But my shoulder hurts
if it makes you feel any better.

21:31.822 --> 21:34.776
- I should have cut your throat!
- Maybe.

21:36.505 --> 21:37.705
But you didn't.

21:37.950 --> 21:40.040
Nelson Clay doesn't have my heroin.

21:40.088 --> 21:43.121
- You've met him?
- No, we tweeted him, you lying prick!

21:43.160 --> 21:45.001
Oh, there you are, you shit for brains.

21:45.121 --> 21:47.387
Romain took off your kit mask, did he, uh?

21:49.205 --> 21:52.200
- I gotta go now, miss you already.
- We will find you!

21:52.232 --> 21:53.598
Ciao!

21:55.275 --> 21:56.747
Son of a bitch!

22:00.313 --> 22:03.045
Excuse me, do you have this in my size?

22:05.253 --> 22:07.270
I have already had

22:07.390 --> 22:10.200
127 hits.

22:10.320 --> 22:13.128
- Well, then your life is now worthwhile.
- Hm.

22:13.146 --> 22:17.350
It's mostly just... samples and
drawings, a few images of pieces I admire,

22:17.367 --> 22:19.600
some of Maddy's photos.

22:19.647 --> 22:23.718
Bastieredesign.com is
alive and kicking. Hm!

22:26.081 --> 22:27.301
You all right?

22:29.256 --> 22:31.568
No. Eh... ah...

22:32.295 --> 22:36.180
I think I may have made
a bit of an ass of myself.

22:36.200 --> 22:37.400
Right...

22:38.557 --> 22:40.357
- He proposed.
- Philip?

22:40.358 --> 22:43.461
